benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request coverage: TC01, TC09, TC14, TC21, TC22 cover successful updates and header variations
Non-existing Resource coverage: TC04, TC15 cover 404 for missing bundle
Concurrency coverage: TC17 tests concurrent updates with conflicts
Validation and error coverage: TC02, TC03, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC11, TC05 cover missing headers, malformed bodies, missing/invalid externalKey, and key conflicts
Edge case payloads: TC10 (long key), TC16 (large payload), TC19 (special characters), TC20 (trailing/leading spaces)
Authorization and security: TC12 covers unauthorized access
Integration and performance coverage: TC13 (503), TC23 (response time under load), TC24 (documentation accessibility)
gaps: Partial Update semantics: no explicit test that disallows partial updates; TC09 allows extra fields which may imply permissiveness
Invalid data types for externalKey not tested (e.g., non-string values)
Internal server error (500) scenarios not explicitly covered; only 503 integration scenario present
Rate limiting / throttling tests are not present
Caching behavior checks (ETag, Cache-Control) are not present
Explicit, deterministic 409 tests for concurrent updates could be strengthened beyond TC17
Explicit validation of error message content in responses could be improved for client compatibility
recommendations: Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error test cases to cover server-side failures
Add tests for invalid data types for externalKey (e.g., numeric or null)
Add rate limiting tests to validate throttling under high load
Add caching validation, including ETag/Cache-Control headers and conditional requests
Clarify and verify PUT semantics for partial updates; if partial updates should be rejected, add tests asserting 400/422 for inappropriate payloads with extra/missing fields
Add explicit, deterministic 409 tests for concurrent updates to ensure consistent conflict resolution
Enhance validation of error messages in responses to ensure consistent client experience and backward compatibility
Maintain and expand accessibility tests (TC24) and consider automated checks for API docs accessibility
